<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-06T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-06T01:00:00-05:00" n="53" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d53">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3–647: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-06T14:00:00+08:00">March 6,
                                    1947—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received March 6—4:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>461. In the course of Minister-Counselor’s<note n="5a" xml:id="d53fn1">W.
                                Walton Butterworth.</note> conversation with the Foreign
                                Minister,<note n="5b" xml:id="d53fn2">Wang Shih-chieh.</note> the
                            Minister-Counselor took occasion to review with him the question of the
                            recent arrests in Peiping, which formed subject matter of Embtel 433,
                            March 3, 7 p.m., and expressed hope that he would use his benevolent
                            influence to prevent the intimidation or repression of liberal elements
                            and to uphold the orderly and legal processes. He agreed to interest
                            himself actively in the matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>